FIFA Players Analysis Dashboard

Key Insights

  • Most players have overall ratings between 61 and 70, indicating a concentrated middle range.
  • The distribution is slightly right-skewed, with fewer players achieving elite ratings (>85).
  • The average overall rating is 65.8, with a standard deviation of 6.9.

Key Insights

  • Younger players (<25 years) tend to have higher potential, often exceeding their current overall rating.
  • Players with high market value (larger bubbles) are typically younger and have high overall ratings (>80).
  • There is a negative correlation between age and potential (r=-0.26), as older players have less room for growth.

Key Insights

  • Overall rating has a strong positive correlation with technical score (r=0.57) and potential (r=0.64).
  • Age has a negative correlation with potential (r=-0.26), indicating younger players have higher growth potential.
  • Market value (value_eur) correlates moderately with overall and potential, reflecting player quality.

Key Insights

  • L. Messi leads with the highest technical score (93.7), excelling in passing, dribbling, and finishing.
  • Top technical players are predominantly attackers, highlighting the importance of technical skills in offensive roles.
  • The top 10 players have technical scores above 86.3, indicating elite performance.

Key Insights

  • Wingers (RW, LW) and attacking midfielders (CAM) have the highest median dribbling scores, typically above 68.0.
  • Defensive positions (CB, CDM) show lower dribbling scores, with medians around 56.0.
  • High variability in dribbling for midfield and attacking roles indicates diverse skill levels.

Key Insights

  • L. Messi excels in dribbling and passing, while Cristiano Ronaldo is stronger in shooting and pace.
  • Both players have well-rounded profiles, with scores above 80 in most attributes.
  • Differences highlight distinct playing styles: technical finesse vs. physical power.

Key Insights

  • Simulated data shows a gradual decline in overall ratings for both Messi and Ronaldo from 2019 to 2022.
  • Messi maintains a slight edge over Ronaldo each year, though both remain elite (>90).
  • The consistent downward trend may reflect aging effects on performance.

Key Insights

  • Center Backs (CB) and Strikers (ST) are the most common positions, making up 30.9% of players.
  • Less common positions like Center Forwards (CF) and Wing Backs (LWELCOME TO FIFA 22 ANALYSISB, RWB) represent under 2.6% of players.
  • The distribution reflects a balance between defensive and offensive roles.

Key Insights

  • The top country by player count is United Kingdom with 1719 players.
  • The top 5 countries account for 31.0% of all players.
  • Player distribution is uneven, with Europe and South America having higher representation.
